parameters: \n<Man's voice>"Hey! Doctor!! Hurry up! Hurry and examine her!"
\n<Man's voice>"Don't dawdle! You all, quickly heal this person!"
\n<Nurse A>"No way... This person is...!? You're joking, right!?"
\n<Nurse B>"How could this happen... What in the world?!"

\n<Man's voice>"Hey, what are you dilly-dallying for!? Quickly treat this
person!"
\n<Nurse A>"I... I understand! Sir Knight, please step back!"

\n<Nurses>"The head injury is severe...!","Stop the bleeding! Press
down on the wound! Bring more cloth!","Can you hear me? Can
you hear my voice!?","No good, she's losing
consciousness--!"

\n<Man's voice>"You lot! Do you understand what will happen if something
goes wrong with this person!? Do you!?"
\n<Nurse A>"Even if you say that! Please just step back!"

\n<Nurse B>"--No good, we need the doctor... Call the medical
practitioner! We need to perform medical arts quickly or she
won't make it!"

\n<Man's voice>"Damn it! Then hurry up and call that medic! Where are
they!?"
\n<Nurse C>"They're in the back room, attending to other patients!"

--A familiar man's shouting voice can be heard. It's the
voice of a knight who was once under my command.

My head hurts terribly. Perhaps due to the searing pain, I
have a rather clear consciousness and remember being
attacked during the military exercise.

Is this what they call one's life flashing before their
eyes? It feels like I'm dreaming, unable to move my limbs at
all. I watch the frantic scene as if it were happening to
someone else.
\n<Nurse A>"--This is bad, she's losing consciousness...!"
\n<Nurse B>"Stay with us! Doctor! Please come quickly, doctor--!"
\n<Knight>"Hey, medical practitioner! What are you dawdling for?"

\n<Luerre>"Stopping treatment to forcibly drag someone out. What are
you thinking? Are you trying to kill a soldier?"

\n<Knight>"I don't care about other soldiers! This person...
Prioritize treating Lady Roselitte!"

\n<Luerre>"Roselitte?... Ah, so this is the rumored royal guard
knight."

\n<Knight>"This person!? You insolent fool, how dare you speak to Lady
Roselitte like that!"

\n<Luerre>"...Indeed it's a dangerous situation, but there are
patients just as critical waiting before her. Her treatment
will have to wait."
\n<Knight>"Don't joke with me! What are you thinking!? "

\n<Luerre>"The one joking here is you... I don't have time to talk
with you. I'm going back."

\n<Knight>"You bastard! Do you mock the Royal Guard Knights? And to
think such behavior is permissible in front of Lady
Roselitte!"

\n<Luerre>"Unfortunately, I am not here as a military doctor but as an
instructor. Therefore, whether it's the Royal Guard Knights
or anyone else, I have no obligation or duty to follow your
orders."

\n<Luerre>"I was only asked to provide medical guidance on-site, and
any treatment I'm providing is purely out of goodwill. Let
me choose my patients."

\n<Knight>"Enough already! Heal Lady Roselitte! Otherwise, I'll cut
you down right here!"

\n<Luerre>"...It seems like you're the one who needs their head
examined first. Sit down quietly over there. I'll properly
examine you later."

\n<Ameria>"Priestess! Please let me examine Lady Roselitte's
injuries!"
\n<Luerre>"...It's too much for you. Help me in the back."

\n<Ameria>"No... It's okay. I can do it. I'll show you that I can heal
her, please!"
\n<Luerre>"No good. You promised to listen to what I say."
\n<Ameria>"But... but! I can't just leave things as they are!"

\n<Luerre>"...Why do you insist on going this far? This person is a
member of the Royal Guard Knights. These knights create
conflicts among themselves, and when they get hurt, they
come crying to doctors like fools."
\n<Luerre>"What do you think this exercise was for?"

\n<Luerre>"Even after the great war, Valam hasn't changed a bit.
Saving a knight will only lead to more bloodshed."

\n<Ameria>"...I understand what you're trying to say, Priestess. But
that doesn't mean it's okay to just leave the knight like
this!"

\n<Ameria>"It's not just the people who are afraid of bandits and
monsters. There are soldiers who fight for their country.
Surely there are many lives saved because of the knights,
right?"
\n<Ameria>"There are so many people who need knights!"

\n<Ameria>"I was saved by a knight in the past, which allowed me to
meet you, Priestess, and become a medical practitioner like
I am today!"

\n<Ameria>"So now it's my turn to help the knight! Now I will be the
one to save those who are hurt!"
Ameria... you not only tried to help me...

"...And this is speculation, but there must be someone
within the empire who orchestrated the attack."

\n<Luerre>"...Ameria. Remember this well. If you say you can heal a
patient and fail to do so, that regret will weigh heavily on
you and cause you suffering."

\n<Luerre>"A medical practitioner needs the resolve to hold people's
lives in their hands and the responsibility to heal them if
they say they will. Choose your next words carefully."

\n<Luerre>"Are you prepared to take on that resolve and
responsibility?"

"If I'm not being protected, then kill me. I don't want to
know anything."
...No, it was me who didn't let you say it...

\n<Luerre>"You examine her. Make sure to heal her. Keep her alive.
Save her. No matter what happens."

\n<Ameria>"Make way, please! I'm going to start the medical
procedure!"

\n<Ameria>"The external wounds are severe... but more than that, it's
inside her head...--Nurse, hold down Lady Roselitte's body!
I'm going to perform a direct procedure on her brain, she'll
likely thrash about!"
\n<Knight>"H-Hey...! Are you really sure about this!?"
\n<Ameria>"Quiet! If your hands are free, help hold her down!"

\n<Ameria>"Lady Roselitte, it's going to be okay. I will definitely
heal you!"

"...The reason it has come to this is because an
inexperienced medical practitioner who participated in the
exercise examined her injuries."
\n<Ameria>"It's okay! It's going to be okay!!"

"I was later informed that if she had received more prompt
and accurate treatment after the examination, there would
have been no lasting aftereffects."

\n<Ameria>"It's okay, it's okay, Roselitte-san! I can heal you, so
I'll do my best, so you have to hang in there...!"
"...But the result is as you see. It's a terrible state."

\n<Ameria>"Roselitte-san! Just a little more! Just a little longer!
Hang in there just a bit more!"
I want to see her again...
I want to see her again... to apologize...
I want to see her again... to say thank you...
"...Perhaps it would have been better if she had died."

\n<???>"Listen to my voice. And entrust your body to it. Then, I
can make your wish come true."
\n<Lyric>"Wake up, Rosé! This is no time to be sleeping so carefree!"
\n<Lyric>"Get up and let's go to Ameria!"

\n<Lyric>"What kind of knight would you be if you're this faint-
hearted! The Rosé I know is much stronger!"

\n<Lyric>"You want to see Ameria, right? Then stand up! Reach out for
my voice! Don't think about giving up over something like
this!"
I also want to help Ameria...
\n<Lyric>"No! 'I want to help Ameria with you!'"
\n<Lyric>"If you reach out for my voice!"
\n<Lyric>"Stand up! You are strong! 'Fight with me!'"

\n<Lyric>"If you're a knight, then fight! Don't let your will to
fight die out! Until your life runs out!"
\n<Lyric>"Respond to my voice with your will to fight! Grab my hand!"
